8 PROPOSED POLICY COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
9 An Act relating to crimes and punishments; amending
21 O.S. 2021, Section 941, as amended by Section 226,
10 Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (21 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
941), which relates to gambling games; expanding
11 scope of crime to include online casino games;
specifying types of providers and suppliers of
12 gambling games; defining terms; and providing an
effective date.
13
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 941, as
18 amended by Section 226, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (21 O.S. Supp.
19 2025, Section 941), is amended to read as follows:
20 Section 941. A. Except as provided in the Oklahoma Charity
21 Games Act, every person who opens, or causes to be opened, or who
22 conducts, whether for hire or not, or carries on either poker,
23 roulette, craps or any banking or percentage, or any gambling game
24 played with dice, cards or any device, including, but not limited
Req. No. 16065 Page 1

1 to, online casino games, for money, checks, credits, or any
2 representatives of value, or who either as owner or employee,
3 geolocation provider, gaming supplier, platform provider, promoter,
4 or media affiliate, whether for hire or not, deals or provides
5 support for those engaged in any such game, shall be guilty of a
6 Class C2 felony offense, and upon conviction thereof, shall be
7 punished by a fine of not less than Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00),
8 nor more than Two Thousand Dollars ($2,000.00), and by imprisonment
9 as provided for in subsections B through F of Section 20M of this
10 title.
11 B. For purposes of this section:
12 1. "Online casino games" means any gambling game that allows a
13 person to access the Internet, World Wide Web, or any part thereof
14 by way of any computer, computer system, computer network, computer
15 software, computer terminal, or similar device including, but not
16 limited to, a cellular or mobile telephone, a smart or electronic
17 watch, or a tablet which, upon risking any representatives of value,
18 simulates any gambling game contemplated in this section or any
19 other form of gambling including, but not limited to, a slot machine
20 as defined in Section 964 of this title, a lottery as defined in
21 subsection A of Section 1051 of this title, a bingo game or U-PIK-EM
22 bingo game as defined in subsections 1 and 22 of Section 402 of
23 Title 3A of the Oklahoma Statutes, and any prohibited game as
24
Req. No. 16065 Page 2

1 cont emplated in subsection H of Section 262 of Title 3A of the
2 Oklahoma Statutes; and
3 2. "Representatives of value" means any and all currency used
4 as part of a dual-currency system of payment allowing a person to
5 exchange such currency for any prize, award, cash, or cash
6 equivalent, or any chance to win any prize, award, cash, or cash
7 equivalent.
8 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
